      "content": "i mean \"temporary disruption\" sounds a bit dismissive of people who have been in coal for generations. if the jobs aren't the same and the towns are dying out, isn't it kind of unfair to say it's just a temporary issue? feels like the bill is basically deciding that their way of life is obsolete for the sake of the environment.",
